summary: Who Cares What They Think? (Keanu Reeves Imagine)
body:
Who Cares What They Think? (Keanu Reeves Imagine)

This was requested.

Summary: You and Keanu Reeves fall in love while starring in a movie together. You start a relationship with the older man and people form their own opinions about it.

There is an age gap in this imagine, but the reader is of age and it is very much legal.

You were on your way to your boyfriend’s house. You were worried because you hadn’t heard from him in several days and that was unlike him. You spoke everyday, but something seemed off with the older man.

You were dating Keanu Reeves. You’d met on the set of a movie that you worked on together. You and Keanu had so much in common. He was laid back and very private, which was something you could relate to. Sure, you might be an actress, but that didn’t mean you didn’t enjoy your privacy. You and Keanu spent so much time together while making the film. You would even hang out a lot off set. You enjoyed each other’s company. He made you happy and you felt that you did the same for him. You could just be yourselves around each other. It wasn’t surprising that feelings developed between you both. Keanu was 54 while you were 30, but the age difference didn’t bother you. It was just a number after all.

You’d played minor roles here and there prior to this movie, but this was your big breakout role. The movie ended up being a huge success and you’d become famous overnight. You found your name being mentioned in several different magazines and your picture plastered on the front covers. It was definitely different than what you were used to, but you were happy that you were being recognized. Maybe people would take you seriously and you would be cast in more serious roles. That had always been your goal as an actress.

However, the fame also brought along unwanted attention and talk. When the media found out about your relationship with Keanu, they latched onto it. The paparazzi would follow you two around, trying to snag pictures of you together. You both were being talked about in gossip magazines and blogs, which was annoying. They mostly spoke of the obvious age difference between the two of you. Some people viewed the relationship as you trying to gain more fame by dating a well known actor while others saw it as Keanu just trying to revive his own career, which was absolutely ridiculous. Keanu didn’t have to revive his career because it was already thriving. People had to find something to talk about and ridicule though. You tried to ignore it all because you viewed it as utter bullshit. As long as you and Keanu knew the truth then who cared what people said?

You pulled into Keanu’s driveway and typed in the code to open his gate. You drove inside once it opened up for you and you parked your car before getting out. You walked up to his door and rang the doorbell. He’d given you a key to use, but you thought that it might be a bad idea to use it since you hadn’t seen or spoken to him in days. You waited a minute before you rang the doorbell again. The door finally opened a few moments later, revealing a casually dressed Keanu. How the man managed to still look breathtaking in such casual wear was beyond you.

“Hey,” you greeted him with a small smile.

“Y/N, hey,” he greeted you back.

“Can I come in?” You asked him.

“Yeah, of course,” he replied and opened the door more as he moved aside so that you could come in.

You stepped inside his house and waited for him to close the door again. He then led you into his living room. He took a seat on the couch and you sat beside him. The atmosphere felt so awkward and you couldn’t figure out why. This was so unusual for you and Keanu. Everything usually felt so right and natural between the two of you.

“Is something wrong, Keanu?” You asked, not bothering with beating around the bush.

“No, why do you ask?” He asked you as he looked at you.

“Well, I haven’t seen you in several days or even heard from you,” you replied. “That’s not like you.”

“I’ve just been busy is all,” he said and shrugged his shoulders. “I’m sorry I’ve been MIA.”

“Are you sure that’s all it is?” You asked him. “Because I feel like there’s something more to it.”

Keanu sighed as he sat back on the couch. You could tell something was bothering him and he seemed to be battling with it. You sat there patiently and waited for him to speak. He would tell you when he was ready.

“It’s just…do you think I’m dragging you down?” He asked you and you raised your brow in confusion.

“What?” You asked him. “What are you talking about, Keanu?”

“Well, I’m obviously older,” he began to explain. “I’m 54 and you’re only 30. You’re still in your prime, Y/N, and I’ve passed mine. Don’t you think that being with me would just hold you back?”

You looked at Keanu as if he were speaking a different language because what he was saying was just preposterous. Why would he think that he was holding you back? He never acted like the whole age difference bothered him before. You both saw yourselves as old souls and didn’t let something like a number come between you. Where would he come up with this?

It hit you suddenly. He had to have read it somewhere. It was the only logical explanation because you knew he wouldn’t come up with something like that on his own.

“You read that somewhere didn’t you?” You asked him and he didn’t say anything. That was answer enough for you. “Keanu, you cant seriously believe the bullshit that the media come up with.”

“I usually don’t,” he finally spoke and then sighed. “It’s just…maybe they’re right. You’ll eventually realize that I’m older and that I’m holding you back…and you’ll leave me.”

You couldn’t believe what you were hearing. Keanu couldn’t seriously believe all of that. He knew you better than those gossip rags, but he was letting them get inside his head and plant false facts inside.

“Let me ask you this,” you began to speak and turned to face him better. “Have I done anything to make you think all of this? That I’ll just up and leave you?”

He thought for a moment then shook his head. “No, you haven’t.”

“And did you only fear all of this after reading about it in some gossip magazine or blog?” You asked him.

“Yeah,” he replied and looked at you then he sighed again. “I’m being a jackass aren’t I?”

You couldn’t help but giggle and shook your head at him. “No, I wouldn’t say you’re being a jackass, babe. You’re just letting the media and gossip get to you when you shouldn’t. It’s understandable, but you should know that it’s comeplete bullshit what they’re saying. Who cares what they think? They don’t know anything about us, Keanu. They only see what they want to because they don’t know the real story. They have to fabricate things.”

Keanu nodded and ran a hand through his beard, which was a nervous habit of his or something he did when he was thinking. “What is the real story then?”

“The real story is that I love you, Keanu,” you told him without even hesitating. It was the first time you had told him that and you meant it. “That girl that they make me out to be in those articles is not the real me. The real me is the person sitting right here, telling you that she loves you and she can’t imagine not being with you. I can be myself around you. I don’t have to pretend to be someone else. You make me a better person.”

Keanu smiled as you spoke, letting your words sink into his brain and knock out the nonsense he had read before. He shouldn’t have let the gossip get to him. He usually didn’t, but he cared about you so much and he was so worried about losing you. It made him insecure reading that stuff, but he should’ve known better. He took your hand in his and kissed it before he squeezed it.

“I love you too, Y/N,” he said as he looked into your eyes, making sure you knew that he meant it. “You’re an amazing woman and I’m happy that you’re in my life. I’m lucky to have you and that you put up with my bullshit. I’m sorry that I ignored you like that and let that stuff get to me.”

You smiled when Keanu told you that he loved you. It made your heart skip a beat as cliche as that might sound. It was true though. He had that affect on you and you absolutely loved it.

“It’s okay,” you told him and moved closer to him so that you could cuddle into him. He moved his arm so that it was wrapped around you and pulled you closer. “I forgive you. Just don’t do that again. Just remember that I love you and I’m not going anywhere. You’re stuck with me.”

“Lucky me,” he replied and smiled as he leaned his head down to kiss you.

You kissed him back and made sure to pour all of the love you had for him into it so that he knew that you truly did love him.
